I"ü<p>If the world is <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/continuous-state-dynamical-systems-share-a-common-structure">chaotic</a>, and <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/representationism-in-cognition-is-adaptationism-in-evolution">if a main function of the brain is to model its environment</a>, then <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/metabolism-influences-neural-dynamics">neural dynamicity</a> might be <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/evolution-is-like-buying-a-suit">an evolutionary advantage</a>. Additionally, bein <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/minds-are-like-mirrors-of-nature">unpredictable</a> (e.g. by predators) might also have an advantage, through an interaction with third-party theory of mind.</p>
